,Recommended,488310,27573249,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,Swilton,"Wow!  Really incredible game.  Once you tweak the settings around for a while (paddle position / power / spin), it feels almost *exactly* like real ping pong.  I'd recommend the power and spin sliders set to about 1/4 of the max value.  When setting the paddle position relative to the controller, try to line up the palm face of the handle to the palm surface of the controller (top surface underneath the menu button).  I found that mating these two surfaces was critical to emulate the real feel.  If the surface of the controller is at any other angle or position, hitting the ball just feels off.  I was expecting latency to kill multiplayer, but they correct for it pretty well.  Real life ping pong skills transfer 1:1 in the game no matter how janky you hit your shots.  Topspin, backspin, sidespin, and even hitting off the edge of the paddle!"
